This statement, issued by the White House Office of the Press Secretary, praises Mayor Thomas M. Menino for his leadership, vision, and compassion in serving the city of Boston for over two decades. It highlights his efforts to revitalize neighborhoods, schools, and businesses, integrate police officers into communities, reduce gun violence, reach out to the homeless and marginalized, and engage young people in the city's life. The statement also mentions that both Mayor Menino and his wife, Angela Menino, have shown a deep love for the city and its people. It concludes by stating that Boston will be a better place to live, work, and raise a family because of the Meninos' service.